  "title": "General manager",
  "description": "<p>· Able to commit night shift/during weekends &amp;PH</p>\n<p>· Able to commit OT</p>\n<p>· Creating long- and short-term plans, including setting targets for milestones, adhering to deadlines and allocating resources</p>\n<p>· Delegating tasks on the project to employees best positioned to complete them</p>\n<p>· Identifying and managing potential risks and liabilities of multiple projects</p>\n<p>· Assisting in the definition of project scope and goals</p>\n<p>· Making effective decisions when presented with multiple options for how to progress with the project</p>\n<p>· Serving as a point of contact for teams when multiple units are assigned to the same project to ensure team actions remain in synergy</p>\n<p>· Communicating with executives or the board to keep the project aligned with their goals</p>\n<p>· Performing quality control on the project throughout development to maintain the standards expected</p>\n<p>· Adjusting schedules and targets on the project as needed</p>\n<p>· Motivating people involved in the project to complete tasks on time</p>\n<h3><strong>Responsibilities</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Oversee day-to-day operations, assign weekly performance goals and ensure their completion, and accomplish your own goals</li>\n  <li>Recruit, onboard, and train high-performing employees to achieve objectives for sales, profitability, and market share</li>\n  <li>Maintain project timelines to ensure tasks are accomplished effectively</li>\n  <li>Develop, implement, and maintain budgetary and resource allocation plans</li>\n  <li>Delegate responsibilities to the best-qualified employees and enforce all policies, procedures, standards, specifications, guidelines, training programs, and cultural values</li>\n  <li>Resolve internal staff conflicts efficiently and to the mutual benefit of all involved</li>\n</ul>",
